      "content": "but \"letting go of a person\" is just a way to say I'm staying alive as a shell of myself. if the version of me that everyone actually liked and respected is truly gone, then the person left behind is just a burden. it’s like the whole thing is just broken beyond repair. if that person is dead, why should the body keep going? shouldn't there be some kind of closure to it?",
